column26: "InclusionHelp": "Add for inclusion 1. Ensure the led bulb has been excluded outside the network. 2. Triggered by OFF ->ON (between 0.5-2 seconds each time) 3. LED solid yellow Color (0xFFFF00) during the pairing(Timeout is 10 seconds).  Failure: Blinks between 100% White and Red 0x0000FF color for 3 seconds (at a rate of 200ms per flash)
column28: the LED should return to a Warm White LED at 100%  Success: Blinks between 100% White and Green 0x00FF00 color for 3 seconds (at a rate of 200ms per flash). Once 3 seconds have passed
column29: the LED should return to a Warm White LED at 100%."
column30: "ExclusionHelp": "Remove for exclusion 1. Assuming led bulb was added to controller. 2. Triggered by OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON (between 0.5-2 seconds each time). 3. LED Solid Purple/Violet Color (0xEE82EE) during the unpairing process. (Timeout is 10 seconds).  Failure: Blinks between 100% White and Red 0x0000FF color for 3 seconds (at a rate of 200ms per flash)
column32: the LED should return to the last color ( memory status(color cc set)) of LED Bulb.  Success: Blinks between 100% White and Blue 0x0000FF color for 3 seconds (at a rate of 200ms per flash). Once 3 seconds have passed
column33: the LED should return to a Warm White LED at 100%."
column34: "ResetHelp": "Reset the Device. 1. Assuming led bulb was added to controller and was power on. 2. RGBW bulb re-power 6 times (between 0.5-2 seconds each time). Note: ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON -> OFF -> ON 3. If the 6th power on
column35: the led bulb change to Yellow color(into pairing process )
column36: which means that the reset factory settings are successf. Using this action in case of the primary controller is missing or inoperable."
